! Architecture

!! Layers

# ''file-upload'' (existing) ‚Äî `<$file-dropzone>` posts the binary to `/api/file-upload-binary`. Server-side MIME-checks against `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/media-types`, computes content hash, routes by MIME via `helpers.js:getSubfolderForType`. file-upload ‚â• 0.1.20 routes `application/vnd.ms-outlook` to `email/`; ‚â• 0.1.24 does the same for `message/rfc822` (`.eml`). Writes to `files/email/<filename>.msg` or `.eml`.
# ''file-pipeline'' (existing) ‚Äî after upload, `widgets/dropzone.js:triggerPipeline()` posts to `/api/file-pipeline`. `pipeline-executor.js` matches `msg.tid` by MIME ‚Äî the pipeline's `match` list contains both `application/vnd.ms-outlook` and `message/rfc822`, so it runs for both formats.
# ''msg-import'' (this plugin) ‚Äî contributes `pipelines/msg.tid` and the runner-actions `convert-msg-body` / `extract-msg-attachments` / `msg-thumb` (merged into `runner-actions.json`).
# ''runner'' (existing) ‚Äî executes the Python extractor `scripts/extract.py`. Pipeline-executor passes `{{input}}` and `{{output}}` as auto-quoted absolute paths.
# ''frontmatter'' (existing) ‚Äî deserializes the `text/x-frontmattered-markdown` artifact tiddler's YAML header into tiddler fields; the save patch writes them back to `.md` on disk.

!! Format dispatch in the extractor

`scripts/extract.py` auto-detects the input format from the filename extension via `_detect_format(input_path)`:

* ''`.eml`'' ‚Üí `parse_eml(input_path)` ‚Äî uses Python's stdlib `email` module (RFC 5322). Returns an `_EmlMsg` adapter that projects `email.message.EmailMessage` through the subset of the `extract-msg` `Message` API used by `run_body` / `run_attachments` / `render_thumbnail` (subject / sender / senderName / to / cc / bcc / date / parsedDate / messageId / inReplyTo / htmlBody / html / body / attachments[] with .cid / .longFilename / .shortFilename / .displayName / .data).
* ''everything else'' (including `.msg`) ‚Üí `extract_msg.openMsg(...)` ‚Äî Outlook binary format, requires the `extract-msg` pip package (lazy import ‚Äî only loaded when actually needed).

The two paths produce structurally-identical objects, so the body / attachments / thumb runners are format-agnostic. The `.eml` path needs no extra pip install ‚Äî only `pandoc` on `PATH` (which is required for both paths to convert the HTML body to markdown).

!! Data flow

```
drop .msg or .eml
  ‚îî‚îÄ‚ñ∂ file-upload ‚Üí files/email/<file>.{msg|eml} + parent tiddler
        ‚îî‚îÄ‚ñ∂ file-pipeline (MIME match: vnd.ms-outlook OR rfc822)
              ‚îú‚îÄ thumb (opt)   ‚Üí magick caption: ‚Üí .png in _generated/
              ‚îú‚îÄ convert       ‚Üí captureStdout   ‚Üí .email tiddler (markdown + YAML)
              ‚îú‚îÄ attachments   ‚Üí scanDir         ‚Üí .attachments/<name> tiddlers
              ‚îî‚îÄ summary (opt) ‚Üí LLM             ‚Üí .summary tiddler
```

!! On-disk layout for one email

```
files/email/
  meeting.msg                            ‚Üê parent
  _derived/
    meeting.msg/
      cid_<id>.png                       ‚Üê inline images (referenced from body)
      att_invoice.pdf                    ‚Üê non-inline attachment (artifact tiddler)
      att_agenda.docx
```

!! Cascade

* ''Delete'' ‚Äî `routes/delete.js` recursively removes `_derived/<basename>/` (incl. nested pipeline products). `_artifact_source` tiddlers (`.email`, `.attachments/*`, optional `.summary`, and any tiddlers produced by nested pipelines like a PDF attachment's `.text` extraction) cascade via `file-upload/startup.js:cascadeDeleteArtifacts`, which walks the chain transitively from file-upload ‚â• 0.1.21.
* ''Rename'' ‚Äî `routes/rename.js` (file-upload ‚â• 0.1.20) renames the `_derived/<basename>/` directory; artifact tiddlers follow via `cascadeRenameArtifacts`, which from 0.1.21 also rewires multi-level descendants (e.g. an attached PDF's thumbnail artifact).
* ''Delete confirm modal'' ‚Äî from file-upload ‚â• 0.1.21, deleting any tiddler with `_canonical_uri` opens a confirmation modal listing the full transitive cascade + every backlinking tiddler. The user can disable via `$:/config/rimir/file-upload/confirm-deletes`.

!! Attachments are first-class

Non-inline attachments are written to `_derived/<basename>/att_<safe-name>`, picked up by file-pipeline's `scanDir`, and turned into artifact tiddlers with `_artifact_source = <parent.msg>`. From file-pipeline ‚â• 0.1.10 each artifact's `type` is inferred from the filename extension (was: every output got `image/png`). After creation, the new `rimir-file-pipeline-artifact-created` hook fires and the `nested-trigger-startup` module re-runs the matching pipeline for each artifact ‚Äî so a PDF attachment gets its own thumbnail + text extraction, and an attached `.msg` gets its own `.email` recursively. Cycle protection: every recursive call carries a `seen` map of URIs already pipelined in the chain.

From file-pipeline 0.1.11 the artifact also inherits the source's `pa.parent` field (orga-apps' note-anchor), so for any cross-cutting query "what tiddlers live in this note" the attachments show up. UI-wise though, the attachments are not exposed as siblings of the email (see next section).

!! Outlook-style inline attachments (`body/email.tid`, ‚â• 0.1.6)

The email's attachments are rendered at the ''top'' of the `.email` view. Three ViewTemplateBody cascades cooperate:

* ''`cascade/msg`'' ‚Äî matches `[type[application/vnd.ms-outlook]]` ‚Üí dispatches to `body/msg` (the parent thumb / expand toggle).
* ''`cascade/eml`'' (new in 0.1.7) ‚Äî matches `[type[message/rfc822]]` ‚Üí dispatches to the same `body/msg` template (the parent thumb / expand toggle works identically for `.eml` files; `body/msg` reads `<currentTiddler>addsuffix[.email]` to locate the artifact, which is format-agnostic).
* ''`cascade/email`'' (new in 0.1.6) ‚Äî matches `[type[text/x-frontmattered-markdown]has[msg-subject]]` ‚Üí dispatches to `body/email`.

`body/email` is the single source of truth for email rendering:

# Attachment row first ‚Äî `[_artifact_source<msgParent>_artifact_type[attachment]]` where `msgParent = {!!_artifact_source}` (the .email's own `_artifact_source` points back at the .msg). The same .msg is the `_artifact_source` of every PDF/image attachment, so the filter naturally finds them.
# Markdown body second ‚Äî `<$transclude $mode="block"/>` renders the .email's `text` field through the frontmatter parser (which forwards to tiddlywiki/markdown).

`body/msg` in "full" mode delegates: `<$tiddler tiddler=<<emailTitle>>><$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/body/email"/></$tiddler>`. So whether the user clicks the .msg thumb in the wiki story river or opens the .email tiddler in a new tab (orga-apps' `#`-permalink pattern), they get the same view.

Tile fallback chain: `_thumbnail_uri` ‚Üí inline `image/*` preview ‚Üí üìÑ emoji + filename. Click on a tile opens the file in a new tab.

Surface separation:

|orga-apps note attachment grid (`views/details.tid`) | Direct uploads only ‚Äî `pa.parent[<note>]!has[_artifact_source]`. The `.msg` shows here. Its inner PDFs do not |
|`body/email.tid` Attachments row (top of email body) | Email's own children ‚Äî `_artifact_source<msg>_artifact_type[attachment]`. The PDFs show here |

This mirrors how a mail client renders attachments ‚Äî the email is one box on the desk, its enclosed files live inside the box ‚Äî rather than spilling them out as separate desk items.

!! ViewTemplateBody cascade

Parent `.msg` / `.eml` tiddlers have `_canonical_uri` pointing at the binary on disk; TW's default body view shows the "Trying to load external content" fallback because no built-in viewer handles `application/vnd.ms-outlook` or `message/rfc822`. msg-import 0.1.3 (+ 0.1.7 for `.eml`) ships:

* ''`$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/cascade/msg`'' ‚Äî tagged `$:/tags/ViewTemplateBodyFilter`, `list-before` the file-upload `cascade/thumbnail`. Matches on `type == application/vnd.ms-outlook` and dispatches to a custom body template.
* ''`$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/cascade/eml`'' ‚Äî same shape, matches on `type == message/rfc822`, dispatches to the same `body/msg` template (the template is format-agnostic ‚Äî it resolves the `.email` artifact via `<currentTiddler>addsuffix[.email]`, which works for both `.msg` and `.eml` parents).
* ''`$:/plugins/rimir/msg-import/body/msg`'' ‚Äî two-mode view sharing the file-upload state tiddler `$:/state/file-upload/view-mode/<title>`:
** ''thumb'' (default): renders `_thumbnail_uri` as a small image; click switches to "full".
** ''full'': transcludes the sibling `<title>.email` tiddler's body (markdown with frontmatter fields). Includes a back-to-thumb button.

The cascade is generic ‚Äî clicking the thumbnail in TW's story river expands to the email body inline. Same template fires when orga-apps' attachment tile click opens the `.email` tiddler in a new tab via the `#`-permalink workaround for appify (see `tw-appify-permalink-workaround` memory).

!! Boundaries (not auto-handled)

* Inline image URLs in the markdown body are wiki-absolute (e.g. `/files/email/_derived/meeting.msg/cid_abc.png`). If a parent `.msg` is renamed, the body's image references are NOT rewritten ‚Äî they still point at the old `_derived/<basename>/` directory until you re-import or hand-edit. Live with it for v0.1; revisit if it bites.
